OL,4,Cadults too sick to work, think tank
OL,5,Cwarns
OL,7,FWhile the labour market is returning
OL,8,Fto normal in terms of pay growth,
OL,9,Fvacancies and unemployment after a
OL,10,F"tumultuous" few years, the Covid-19
OL,11,Fpandemic has left an "alarming" legacy
OL,12,Fof rising long-term sickness, the
OL,13,Freport warns.JThe number of working-
OL,14,Fage adults economically inactive due
OL,15,Fto ill health rose from 2.1 million in
OL,16,FJuly 2019 to a peak of 2.8 million by
OL,17,FOctober 2023, before falling slightly
OL,18,Fto 2.7 million in December 2023, the
OL,19,Ffoundation reported.
